<dl><dt>ChumBox</dt>
<dd><p>A <strong>Chum box</strong> (or <em>chumbucket</em>) is a format of <a title="Online advertising" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Online_advertising">Online advertising</a> that uses a grid of thumbnails and captions to drive traffic to other sites and webpages. This form of advertising is often associated with low quality '<a title="Clickbait" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clickbait">clickbait</a>' links and articles.</p></dd>
</dl>
<p>The term derives from fishing terms such as <a title="Chumming" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chumming">chumming</a> &ndash; referring to the use of (fish) meat as a lure for fish.</p>

